The Proculians argued the case on the analogy of occupatio, and regarded the giver of the form as the owner os the product; a view which seems to have commended itself to Ulpian (‘ mutata forma prope interimit substantiam rei ’ Dig. 10. 4. 9. 3). The Sabinians viewed it as a kind of accessio, and denied any transfer of ownership, Gaius ii. 99. The intermediate opinion, confirmed by Justinian‚ is found in Gaius (Dig. 41. 1. 77), Paulus (ib. 24), and other juristS.
